==English==

===Etymology===
Derived from Greek '''μονοθεϊσμός''' ('''monotheïsmós'''), from '''μονός''' ('''monós''') meaning "one" + '''θεós''' ('''theós''') meaning "god" or "deity" + English '''–ism'''

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-monotheism.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}
# The belief in a [[single]] [[god]], [[deity]], [[spirit]], etc. ; especially within an [[organize]]d [[religion]], [[faith]], or [[creed]].

